Task #10: Increase rewriter word budget to 300, add mandatory detailed outfit rule

Changes made to groq_ai.py and ollama_ai.py system prompts:

1. Word budget: changed from "20-70 words" (groq) / "20-60 words" (ollama) to
   "150-300 words" in both files. This forces the rewriter to produce rich,
   complete prompts instead of bare-bones 30-word outputs.

2. OUTFIT rule added (mandatory): new rule inserted after COMPLEXION/SKIN TONE rule
   in groq_ai.py and after EYELASHES rule in ollama_ai.py. Rule requires:
   - Garment types with full names (not vague labels like "uniform")
   - Colors of each garment piece
   - Materials/textures if visible
   - Distinctive features (buttons, zippers, lace, trim, patterns)
   - Layering order and fit
   - All accessories (belt, tie, hat, gloves, bag, jewelry, wrist cuffs, socks, shoes)
   - Example output included in the rule for the model to follow
   - Explicit prohibition: "Never reduce outfit to a single vague word"

No other logic changes. Only system prompt strings were modified.
